body:
So I had a dream last night that snape was teaching me a spell to stop me from feeling sad (I mean just try to picture snape cheering someone up to begin with). I was crying but he told me to say the spell (I don’t remember what it is) and then the wand movement for it was an infinity symbol ♾. So I did it and was feeling better and it wasn’t until I woke did I realize the full meaning of the infinity symbol

♾ =always

summary: I am sorry if I am offending anybody by posting this, but jily practically doesn’t make any sense. I don’t even know why people...
body:
I am sorry if I am offending anybody by posting this, but jily practically doesn’t make any sense. I don’t even know why people ship it so much.

I didn’t ship it when I was a kid, and I still don’t. I suppose when I was a kid that just loved watching Harry Potter, it was just there? If that makes any sense. It wasn’t until a few years earlier when I started reinvesting in HP that I actually started hating it. Not only it’s a hugely problematic ship, but it’s also everywhere? No thanks. I’d rather stick with my crack ships.

Anyway, thank you for coming to my TED talk. Have a good day.

summary: It's time to introduce to you the next animal! This is probably the most dangerous beast that have ever inhabited our land. This...
body:
It’s time to introduce to you the next animal! This is probably the most dangerous beast that have ever inhabited our land. This is Bayun-cat. If he were not be so lazy, he could rule the world. Bayun-cat represents wild cats, which are almost impossible to domesticate. If someone assures you that he was able to domesticate the Bayun-cat, then most likely that this Bayun-cat domesticated him itself, and skillfully convinced him to the contrary. Bayun-cats are solitary animals. Most of the time they spend alone and in a dream. Make no mistakes: the size of this predator is quite small - slightly larger than a big domestic cat. The cat has incredible strength and claw-sharp blades. It can kill an adult bear on its own! The cat has incredible eyes that resemble blueberry berries.

I do not advise you to look into them! They are fascinating. Many travelers met a cat in the forest. Once looking into its eyes, they were unable to look away. Cat’s wool is thick and weightless like a fog. Usually it’s gray or dark brown. Bayun-cat has its name for a reason. Its rumbling can immerse you into a deep sleep. This rumbling, like the look of a cat, is almost impossible to resist. So you plunge into your sweetest sleep and go on a journey through the personal dreamworld..

And at this moment the cat eats you.. Unless, of course, it will find a reason to leave you alive. The characteristic rumbling that fills everything around you allows you to realize that you’re in a dream!

Most often, bayun-cat prefers to hunt for the Gamayun bird. The cat, using its abilities, confuses bird‘s thoughts. It fall asleep and drop to the ground dead. Gamayun becomes easy prey for a cat, especially at night, when the predator prefers to hunt.

I know people who manage to do business, recording the rumbling of a cat on vinyl records and selling them as a remedy for insomnia. I don’t know how it helps to avoid insomnia, but, apparently, the business of people is going well.
